1
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:12,291
[SHIGARAKI]
Kill the Symbol of Peace.

2
00:00:12,375 --> 00:00:14,708
All Might.

3
00:00:14,791 --> 00:00:16,500
[KUROGIRI]
It's a pleasure to meet you.

4
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:18,500
We are the League of Villains.

5
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:22,750
I know it's impolite, but we
decided to invite ourselves in

6
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:26,000
to this haven of
justice to say hello.

7
00:00:26,083 --> 00:00:28,708
And besides, isn't
this a fitting place

8
00:00:28,791 --> 00:00:33,291
for All Might, the Symbol of
Peace, to take his last breath?

9
00:00:33,375 --> 00:00:34,916
[grunts]

10
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,625
[TENYA]
What's going on?

11
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:39,208
[VILLAIN A] Idiots, that's
Eraser Head! A pro!

12
00:00:39,291 --> 00:00:43,041
He can cancel your Quirks
just by looking at you.

13
00:00:43,125 --> 00:00:43,916
[THIRTEEN]
Class rep!

14
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:44,916
Yes?

15
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,500
[THIRTEEN]
I have a job for you.

16
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:49,000
Run to the school and tell the
faculty what's going on here.

17
00:00:49,083 --> 00:00:50,500
Yes, but--

18
00:00:50,583 --> 00:00:52,625
It would be disgraceful for
me to leave you all behind.

19
00:00:52,708 --> 00:00:54,541
[THIRTEEN]
Use your Quirk to save others.

20
00:00:54,625 --> 00:00:56,125
Be a real hero!

21
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:03,958
[THIRTEEN]
Black Hole!

22
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:08,625
[MINETA gasps] What do you
mean "fight"? Are you crazy?!

23
00:01:08,708 --> 00:01:09,875
[gasps]

24
00:01:09,958 --> 00:01:13,791
[IZUKU] Now's our chance.
We can beat them!

25
00:01:13,875 --> 00:01:14,750
[IZUKU yells]

26
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:18,708
Take this! Delaware Smash!

27
00:01:21,625 --> 00:01:25,916
[SEA VILLAINS screaming]

28
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,583
[yelling] Take this,
you villains!

29
00:01:29,666 --> 00:01:31,791
You can eat my sticky balls!

30
00:01:34,625 --> 00:01:36,083
[HALF-FISH VILLAIN A]
Move!

31
00:01:36,166 --> 00:01:37,333
--[SEA VILLAIN A] Get off me!
--[SEA VILLAIN B] I'm stuck!

32
00:01:37,416 --> 00:01:38,750
[HALF-FISH VILLAIN A]
You're gonna drown me!

33
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,708
Not too shabby.

34
00:01:42,791 --> 00:01:46,291
You guys are amazing.
Both of you.

35
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:50,416
[TSUYU] I guess we passed
the shipwreck zone.

36
00:03:25,458 --> 00:03:27,333
[MINETA chuckles]
I had a good poop this morning,

37
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:30,625
which makes my balls stickier.
They're not goin' anywhere!

38
00:03:30,708 --> 00:03:32,833
Can't believe we managed
to get all of 'em at once.

39
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:34,833
It took everything I had
to keep my composure.

40
00:03:34,916 --> 00:03:37,208
It was such a gamble, what if
they'd had reserves underwater

41
00:03:37,291 --> 00:03:38,583
that we didn't know
about? They could've...

42
00:03:38,666 --> 00:03:40,041
[TSUYU]
You're creeping me out.

43
00:03:40,125 --> 00:03:41,583
Stop it. Please.

44
00:03:41,666 --> 00:03:42,958
[IZUKU]
Uh--

45
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:44,750
[TSUYU] Instead of second
guessing what we did,

46
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:46,333
shouldn't we think
about our next move?

47
00:03:46,416 --> 00:03:49,250
Yeah. You're
totally right. Ah--

48
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:51,583
[TSUYU]
Are you okay?

49
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:54,583
Yeah. Fine. Don't
worry about me.

50
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:57,000
We should make getting
help our top priority!

51
00:03:57,083 --> 00:03:58,833
If we follow the
shore to the exit,

52
00:03:58,916 --> 00:04:02,000
then we can avoid the
central plaza entirely.

53
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:03,166
Good idea.

54
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,875
That way we don't
run into the villains

55
00:04:04,958 --> 00:04:07,708
Mr. Aizawa's facing
off with there.

56
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:12,916
[IZUKU] Yeah, but, can he
handle them on his own?

57
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:17,541
How long can he hold out
against a big group like that?

58
00:04:17,625 --> 00:04:19,125
If he doesn't get some backup,

59
00:04:19,208 --> 00:04:21,000
then he's just going
to overexert himself.

60
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:22,625
He'll end up defeated
by those villains

61
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:24,166
'cause he was trying
to keep us safe.

62
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:28,541
[gasps] Wait. Don't tell me
you're suggesting...?

63
00:04:28,625 --> 00:04:31,083
Are you trying to get
us killed or something?

64
00:04:31,166 --> 00:04:32,250
I'm not saying that we should

65
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:34,375
jump into the middle
of a battle. But...

66
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:36,541
Maybe we can find a way to
take a few of those guys out

67
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:38,875
and lighten his load.

68
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:41,208
[IZUKU] We'd had our first
real fight and won,

69
00:04:41,291 --> 00:04:43,291
but that only
gave us false hope.

70
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:45,041
It made us think our
powers could actually

71
00:04:45,125 --> 00:04:46,625
work against the enemy.

72
00:04:46,708 --> 00:04:48,916
We'd soon learn
how wrong we were.

73
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:58,375
[TODOROKI] So the plan was to
scatter us, and then kill us.

74
00:04:58,458 --> 00:05:00,750
You were woefully unprepared.

75
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,541
In fact, it looks to me as
though you've had no training.

76
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:07,833
You haven't the slightest
idea how to use your Quirks.

77
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:08,916
This power...

78
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,625
He froze us the instant
we warped here.

79
00:05:10,708 --> 00:05:13,291
[LANDSLIDE VILLAIN B]
He's not a kid, he's a monster!

80
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:15,416
So cold...

81
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:17,833
[SHIGARAKI]
Where is he?

82
00:05:17,916 --> 00:05:20,583
I went through the trouble
of bringing so many friends

83
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:22,791
who're eager to meet him.

84
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:25,416
[TODOROKI] How do they
plan to kill All Might?

85
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:26,958
At first I thought
they'd gathered

86
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:29,708
a force of elite criminals who
could simply overpower him.

87
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:31,625
[yells]

88
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:38,375
[TODOROKI] But that can't
possibly be their master plan.

89
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:40,833
Most these villains
are low-level thugs.

90
00:05:40,916 --> 00:05:41,833
Just pawns.

91
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:43,708
[LANDSLIDE VILLAIN E groans]

92
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:47,000
[TODOROKI]
From what I can tell,

93
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:51,500
there are only four or five
truly dangerous people here.

94
00:05:51,583 --> 00:05:53,958
If that's the case,
then what we need right now

95
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:56,500
is more information.

96
00:05:56,583 --> 00:05:57,791
Listen well.

97
00:05:57,875 --> 00:05:59,625
If you stay frozen,
your cells will slowly die

98
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:02,041
as your body succumbs to
frostbite and hypothermia.

99
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:03,375
[LANDSLIDE VILLAINS whimper]

100
00:06:03,458 --> 00:06:06,250
[TODOROKI] Luckily for you,
I wanna be a hero.

101
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:09,250
So I'd like to avoid
any unnecessary cruelty.

102
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,041
But I can only do
that if you tell me

103
00:06:13,125 --> 00:06:15,000
how you plan to kill All Might.

104
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:17,166
That's the only way
you'll survive.

105
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:21,708
[screams]

106
00:06:21,791 --> 00:06:23,166
[MOUNTAIN VILLAIN A grunts]

107
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:24,583
These dudes are terrifying!

108
00:06:24,666 --> 00:06:26,291
My whole life just
flashed before my eyes,

109
00:06:26,375 --> 00:06:29,333
I think I saw the grim
reaper! What's going on?

110
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:31,416
Could you maybe take it
down a few notches?

111
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,666
[YAOYOROZU]
Right now we need to focus on

112
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,500
getting away from these enemies.

113
00:06:34,583 --> 00:06:36,250
Then pull out a
weapon for me, too!

114
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:38,000
You're the one with
electrical powers.

115
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:39,250
Just zap 'em so we can run.

116
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,500
Were you not paying attention

117
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:43,041
during combat training?
Some partner you were.

118
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:45,000
I can cover my body
with electricity.

119
00:06:45,083 --> 00:06:47,416
But if I try to shoot it out,
it'll go everywhere!

120
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:48,916
I'd take you guys down
along with them!

121
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,208
Or did you want
shock treatment today?

122
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:52,541
I can't even call
for help because

123
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,833
there's still interference
jamming the signal!

124
00:06:54,916 --> 00:06:56,291
I'm counting on you two.

125
00:06:56,375 --> 00:06:57,833
I'm no help in this situation.

126
00:06:57,916 --> 00:06:59,541
You've gotta get us
outta here. Please!

127
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:02,291
You're a real damsel
in distress, aren't you?

128
00:07:02,375 --> 00:07:03,458
Uh-- Ah!

129
00:07:03,541 --> 00:07:06,083
[JIRO] New idea. You're
my human stun gun.

130
00:07:06,166 --> 00:07:07,458
Seriously? Come o--

131
00:07:07,541 --> 00:07:08,750
[MOUNTAIN VILLAIN A groans]

132
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:11,875
Whoa. Hey, this is working!
I'm super strong!

133
00:07:11,958 --> 00:07:14,041
Sit back, you two.
You can count on me!

134
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:15,750
[JIRO]
You are exhausting.

135
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:16,916
[gasps]

136
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,500
Try electrocuting
solid rock, kid!

137
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,208
[KAMINARI groans]

138
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:27,291
[MOUNTAIN VILLAINS yelp]

139
00:07:27,375 --> 00:07:28,166
[grunts]

140
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:29,875
[yelps]

141
00:07:29,958 --> 00:07:31,708
[MOUNTAIN VILLAINS screaming]

142
00:07:31,791 --> 00:07:33,625
You're lucky that
worked out so well.

143
00:07:33,708 --> 00:07:34,791
I'm sorry.

144
00:07:34,875 --> 00:07:37,500
Next time I'll ask
before saving our butts.

145
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:40,708
[PRESENT MIC] Kyoka Jiro!
Her Quirk: Earphone Jack!

146
00:07:40,791 --> 00:07:41,958
She can turn her own heartbeats

147
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:43,791
into explosively
amplified sound waves

148
00:07:43,875 --> 00:07:45,250
by inserting her plugs!

149
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:47,375
Plus, she can hear
really quiet sounds.

150
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:48,666
So hip!

151
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,041
[JIRO]
Damn it, Kaminari.

152
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:51,708
You couldn't have asked for
some kind of aiming gear

153
00:07:51,791 --> 00:07:55,000
when you put in your costume
request form? I mean, come on!

154
00:07:56,791 --> 00:07:58,583
[grunts] It's ready!

155
00:07:58,666 --> 00:07:59,791
[JIRO gasps]

156
00:07:59,875 --> 00:08:01,750
[YAOYOROZU]
It takes me a little longer...

157
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:04,250
to create an object this big!

158
00:08:05,041 --> 00:08:06,333
[MOUNTAIN VILLAIN H]
A blanket?

159
00:08:06,416 --> 00:08:08,750
[MOUNTAIN VILLAIN I]
Is it supposed to be a shield?

160
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:10,708
You're looking at a
sheet of insulation

161
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:13,916
100 millimeters thick.
Go, Kaminari.

162
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,208
Heh. Badass.

163
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:18,916
[KAMINARI]
Now I don't have to worry about

164
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,625
hurting my friends.
You guys are fried!

165
00:08:22,708 --> 00:08:25,625
[MOUNTAIN VILLAINS screaming]

166
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:31,916
[YAOYOROZU]
Now then.

167
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,166
I'm worried about
the rest of our class.

168
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:35,541
We should find them right away.

169
00:08:35,625 --> 00:08:38,416
You're looking a little
overexposed right now!

170
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:40,750
Huh? I can make
some new clothes.

171
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,333
[PRESENT MIC]
Momo Yaoyorozu.

172
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:44,291
Her Quirk: Creation!

173
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:47,333
She can create any
non-living object she wants!

174
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:49,500
But she's only able to do
this if she understands

175
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:52,750
the molecular structure
of the item she's making.

176
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:55,416
[JIRO]
Yaoyorozu is so punk rock.

177
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,833
Huh? Kaminari,
don't you dare look!

178
00:08:58,916 --> 00:08:59,500
[YAOYOROZU]
Uh...

179
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:03,041
[KAMINARI laughing]

180
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:05,791
[PRESENT MIC]
Denki Kaminari: Electrification!

181
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:07,291
When he goes over
his wattage limit,

182
00:09:07,375 --> 00:09:08,458
his brain short circuits

183
00:09:08,541 --> 00:09:10,375
and he becomes a huge
idiot for a while!

184
00:09:10,458 --> 00:09:12,375
Listen to him babbling!

185
00:09:16,875 --> 00:09:18,875
[MINETA whispering] Remember,
Midoriya, we're just here to see

186
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:20,500
how things are going, right?

187
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:21,250
[TSUYU whispering]
Ribbit.

188
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:22,708
[IZUKU]
Yeah, I know.

189
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:25,541
We'll get outta here the
second it seems dangerous.

190
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:30,041
--[AIZAWA grunting]
--[VILLAINS groaning]

191
00:09:31,875 --> 00:09:33,250
[VILLAINS groan]

192
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:36,750
[AIZAWA grunts]

193
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:38,416
[gasps]

194
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,041
[SHIGARAKI]
First it was 23 seconds.

195
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:41,583
Final boss.

196
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,625
[SHIGARAKI]
Then it was 24 seconds.

197
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:46,791
And then 20. Then 17.

198
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:49,375
[grunts]

199
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:51,166
[ALL gasp]

200
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:54,958
[AIZAWA pants]

201
00:09:55,041 --> 00:09:56,041
[SHIGARAKI]
It was hard to see

202
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:57,916
when you were jumping around,

203
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:02,458
but I've found your
tell. It's your hair.

204
00:10:02,541 --> 00:10:05,958
When it drops, it means you've
stopped using your Quirk.

205
00:10:06,041 --> 00:10:08,375
You're having
to blink more often.

206
00:10:08,458 --> 00:10:10,666
Don't push yourself
too hard, now.

207
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:12,791
You might just fall apart.

208
00:10:12,875 --> 00:10:15,333
Wouldn't that be a shame?

209
00:10:17,791 --> 00:10:19,041
[gasps]

210
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,125
[AIZAWA grunts]

211
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:22,625
[AIZAWA]
He destroyed my elbow.

212
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:24,250
[VILLAIN D grunting]

213
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:27,791
[AIZAWA, VILLAINS grunting]

214
00:10:27,875 --> 00:10:29,250
[AIZAWA panting]

215
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:31,291
[SHIGARAKI] That annoying
Quirk of yours isn't suited

216
00:10:31,375 --> 00:10:35,000
for drawn-out fights
against big groups, is it?

217
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:36,208
Don't you think you're a little

218
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:38,875
out of your element
here, Eraser Head?

219
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:41,750
You're much better
at working stealthily.

220
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:43,541
You're known for
surprise attacks,

221
00:10:43,625 --> 00:10:46,125
not fighting head-to-head.

222
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:47,625
[panting]

223
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:49,500
[SHIGARAKI] But despite knowing
that, you didn't hesitate

224
00:10:49,583 --> 00:10:51,833
to jump into the
middle of this fight.

225
00:10:51,916 --> 00:10:53,541
To put your students at ease.

226
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:55,208
[SNAIL-EYES VILLAIN A grunts]

227
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:59,125
--[AIZAWA grunting]
--[VILLAINS groaning]

228
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:01,000
[AIZAWA panting]

229
00:11:01,083 --> 00:11:03,958
[grunting, panting]

230
00:11:04,041 --> 00:11:06,833
[SHIGARAKI] And look at you,
you're still standing!

231
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:09,666
You really are so cool!

232
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:12,708
[SHIGARAKI]
Oh, by the way, hero.

233
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:14,333
[gasps]

234
00:11:14,416 --> 00:11:17,208
[SHIGARAKI]
I am not the final boss.

235
00:11:19,125 --> 00:11:20,708
[AIZAWA grunts]

236
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:24,125
--[gasps]
--[thuding]

237
00:11:24,208 --> 00:11:27,375
--No, Mr. Aizawa...
--[thuding]

238
00:11:27,458 --> 00:11:31,458
[KUROGIRI] Ah, Black Hole,
the Quirk that sucks up matter

239
00:11:31,541 --> 00:11:35,750
and turns it to dust.
Such an astounding power.

240
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:39,166
However, you're a
rescue hero, Thirteen,

241
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:41,916
skilled at saving
people from disasters.

242
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,500
Consequently, that
means you have

243
00:11:44,583 --> 00:11:48,583
little fighting experience
or battlefield awareness.

244
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:51,125
[THIRTEEN yelps]

245
00:11:51,208 --> 00:11:52,958
[STUDENTS gasping]

246
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,833
[THIRTEEN]
He opened a warp gate!

247
00:11:55,916 --> 00:11:57,333
[KUROGIRI chuckles]

248
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:01,958
[KUROGIRI]
How unfortunate.

249
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:03,833
You've turned
yourself into dust.

250
00:12:03,916 --> 00:12:06,166
[STUDENTS gasping]

251
00:12:08,791 --> 00:12:12,041
[THIRTEEN]
I'm sorry. He got me.

252
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:13,958
Thirteen!

253
00:12:14,041 --> 00:12:17,083
Iida, get outta here! Go! Now!

254
00:12:17,166 --> 00:12:18,291
U-Uh--

255
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:19,625
[THIRTEEN]
Use your Quirk to save others.

256
00:12:19,708 --> 00:12:21,500
Be a real hero!

257
00:12:21,583 --> 00:12:24,291
[grunts]

258
00:12:26,291 --> 00:12:29,791
Engine!

259
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:32,625
[KUROGIRI] A sheep trying
to escape from the wolves.

260
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:35,166
I simply can't allow that.

261
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:36,666
[pants]

262
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,916
[KUROGIRI] If other heroes
arrive, it'll be harder for us

263
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,291
to put an end to All Might.

264
00:12:43,416 --> 00:12:45,333
[TENYA]
This responsibility...

265
00:12:47,041 --> 00:12:50,125
[TENYA]
...was entrusted to me!

266
00:12:50,208 --> 00:12:53,791
Classmates! I'll keep you safe!

267
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:57,791
[SHOJI]
Run!

268
00:12:57,875 --> 00:12:58,666
[TENYA gasps]

269
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:00,458
[SHOJI]
I've got him!

270
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:01,583
[TENYA grunts]

271
00:13:01,666 --> 00:13:03,791
[TENYA]
I'll be back in a flash!

272
00:13:03,875 --> 00:13:05,666
[KUROGIRI]
You impertinent child!

273
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,500
[gasps]

274
00:13:07,583 --> 00:13:09,583
[KUROGIRI] You won't set
foot outside those doors!

275
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:11,958
[TENYA] I'm close!
But what if it's locked?

276
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:13,916
Will I be able to
pry it open in time?

277
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,875
[KUROGIRI]
I have no time for this.

278
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,083
[KUROGIRI]
Be gone!

279
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,583
[TENYA grunts]

280
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:22,833
[IZUKU]
This was it.

281
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:24,666
Ya see? Good as new.

282
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:27,208
[IZUKU]
The evil that pros faced...

283
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:31,416
We'd gotten our first look,
but the worst was yet to come.

284
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,458
[AIZAWA gasping]

285
00:13:33,541 --> 00:13:37,875
[SHIGARAKI] What do you
think of him, Eraser Head?

286
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:40,791
Hm... He's the bioengineered,

287
00:13:40,875 --> 00:13:45,541
anti-Symbol of Peace.
But you can call him "Nomu."

288
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:49,375
[shrieks]

289
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:01,208
Say goodbye!

290
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:04,333
[VILLAINS groan]

291
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:08,958
--[KIRISHIMA grunting]
--[VILLAIN I groaning]

292
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:11,666
[KIRISHIMA, KATSUKI panting]

293
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:13,375
Think that's the
last of these guys.

294
00:14:13,458 --> 00:14:14,458
Buncha weaklings.

295
00:14:14,541 --> 00:14:15,666
All right.

296
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,458
Let's hurry and find
the rest of our class.

297
00:14:17,541 --> 00:14:19,583
If we're both still in the USJ,

298
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:21,583
then everyone else
probably is, too.

299
00:14:21,666 --> 00:14:24,375
And not all of them have
the offensive skills we do.

300
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:26,208
We gotta make sure they're safe.

301
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:28,000
Especially since we
screwed things up

302
00:14:28,083 --> 00:14:29,375
when we got in the way earlier.

303
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:31,625
If Thirteen had been able
to suck up that villain,

304
00:14:31,708 --> 00:14:33,791
then we never would've
been separated like that.

305
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:35,458
We have to make it up
to the others!

306
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,791
You wanna track
everyone down, have fun.

307
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:40,541
But I'm gonna go destroy
that warpy bastard.

308
00:14:40,625 --> 00:14:41,750
Huh?

309
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,875
Our physical attacks
didn't hurt that guy.

310
00:14:43,958 --> 00:14:45,666
C'mon. Don't be an idiot, man.

311
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:47,166
[KATSUKI]
Shut up!

312
00:14:47,250 --> 00:14:50,041
I'm gonna take him down because
he's their way in and out.

313
00:14:50,125 --> 00:14:52,291
If I cut off their escape
route, they'll be stuck here

314
00:14:52,375 --> 00:14:53,958
and have to pay for
what they've done.

315
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:55,458
We'll just have
to figure it out.

316
00:14:55,541 --> 00:14:57,291
[CAMOUFLAGE VILLAIN A]
Hope you had fun chit-chatting.

317
00:14:57,375 --> 00:14:59,166
Too bad you let
your guard down--

318
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:01,666
[CAMOUFLAGE VILLAIN A screams]

319
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:03,208
[KATSUKI]
Anyway.

320
00:15:03,291 --> 00:15:05,583
If all these villains are small
fries like these guys were,

321
00:15:05,666 --> 00:15:07,708
then our classmates
can handle 'em.

322
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:10,208
[KIRISHIMA]
That reaction time was insane.

323
00:15:10,291 --> 00:15:11,458
Also...

324
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:13,791
Since when do you act
so calm and rational?

325
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:15,250
Usually you're all like...

326
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:18,083
[KATSUKI]
Die! Die! Die!

327
00:15:18,166 --> 00:15:20,583
I'm always calm and rational,
you red-haired loser!

328
00:15:20,666 --> 00:15:22,166
Yeah! There you are.

329
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,916
[KATSUKI grunts] Go find the
others if you want to.

330
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,458
Wait, hold up!

331
00:15:26,541 --> 00:15:28,000
I think what
you're really saying

332
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:31,291
is that you believe
in our classmates.

333
00:15:31,375 --> 00:15:34,125
And that's thinkin'
like a man, Bakugo.

334
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:39,000
[FIRE VILLAIN A]
Damn it! He's too fast!

335
00:15:41,875 --> 00:15:43,166
[FIRE VILLAIN A groans]

336
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:45,166
[FIRE VILLAIN B]
I see 'im. Up there!

337
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,166
[OJIRO]
I have to help the others.

338
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:52,958
[SQUALL ZONE VILLAIN A]
We found you!

339
00:15:53,041 --> 00:15:55,125
[SQUALL ZONE VILLAINS yell]

340
00:15:55,208 --> 00:15:58,500
[SQUALL ZONE VILLAINS groan]

341
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,500
That's six of them down.

342
00:16:01,916 --> 00:16:04,916
We're reducing their
numbers, but very slowly.

343
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,250
I hope it helps in the long run.

344
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:11,625
[KUROGIRI]
I have no time for this.

345
00:16:11,708 --> 00:16:13,625
Be gone!

346
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,041
[TENYA gasps]

347
00:16:19,125 --> 00:16:20,125
[KUROGIRI gasps]

348
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:21,291
[OCHACO]
I don't know what his Quirk is,

349
00:16:21,375 --> 00:16:23,291
but he's wearing some
kinda weird armor.

350
00:16:23,375 --> 00:16:27,333
So he must have a physical
body inside here somewhere.

351
00:16:27,416 --> 00:16:29,875
Now! Run, Iida!

352
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:32,375
[KUROGIRI]
You pest! How dare you!

353
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:37,125
[TENYA grunts]

354
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:38,041
[KUROGIRI]
I've got you!

355
00:16:38,125 --> 00:16:39,666
Not so fast!

356
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:42,291
[SATO grunts]

357
00:16:45,541 --> 00:16:48,125
[SATO grunting]

358
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:50,791
[SATO]
Go!

359
00:16:50,875 --> 00:16:53,083
[TENYA grunts]

360
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:55,166
[KUROGIRI growls]

361
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:57,791
[TENYA]
Engine... Boost!

362
00:17:03,125 --> 00:17:05,875
[KUROGIRI]
He's going to call for backup.

363
00:17:07,125 --> 00:17:08,958
[KUROGIRI]
It's over.

364
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:14,333
[AIZAWA groaning]

365
00:17:14,416 --> 00:17:16,416
[yelps]

366
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,958
[SHIGARAKI]
You can erase peoples' powers.

367
00:17:19,041 --> 00:17:22,083
That's irritating, but
it's nothing impressive.

368
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,958
When faced with true,
devastating power,

369
00:17:25,041 --> 00:17:27,208
you might as well be
a Quirkless child.

370
00:17:27,291 --> 00:17:29,875
[AIZAWA panting]

371
00:17:29,958 --> 00:17:32,375
[screams]

372
00:17:33,666 --> 00:17:37,166
[AIZAWA] He's breaking my
bones like they're twigs.

373
00:17:37,250 --> 00:17:39,416
I'm positive I erased his Quirk.

374
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:42,875
That means he's super strong,
even without powers.

375
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:44,875
[AIZAWA groans]

376
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:47,666
[AIZAWA] I think he's
as strong as All Might.

377
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:49,291
[AIZAWA groans]

378
00:17:49,375 --> 00:17:51,875
[MINETA]
No... No!

379
00:17:51,958 --> 00:17:54,166
I can't watch this anymore.

380
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:57,333
We should be getting out of
here super-fast, shouldn't we?

381
00:17:57,416 --> 00:17:58,750
[TSUYU]
Ribbit.

382
00:18:02,416 --> 00:18:04,208
[KUROGIRI]
Tomura Shigaraki.

383
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:07,791
[SHIGARAKI] Kurogiri, did you
manage to kill Thirteen?

384
00:18:07,875 --> 00:18:10,208
[KUROGIRI] The rescue hero
is out of commission.

385
00:18:10,291 --> 00:18:12,583
But there were students
I was unable to disperse

386
00:18:12,666 --> 00:18:15,375
and one of them got
outside of the facility.

387
00:18:15,458 --> 00:18:16,666
[SHIGARAKI]
Huh?!

388
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:28,833
[SHIGARAKI growling, panting]

389
00:18:28,916 --> 00:18:33,083
[SHIGARAKI]
Kurogiri... You fool...

390
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:35,208
If you weren't our warp gate,

391
00:18:35,291 --> 00:18:38,666
I'd tear apart every
last atom in your body.

392
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:40,083
[SHIGARAKI grunts]

393
00:18:42,708 --> 00:18:45,083
[SHIGARAKI] There's no way
we can win if dozens of pros

394
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:48,166
show up to stop us.
It's game over.

395
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:50,250
Back to the title screen.

396
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:53,166
And I was looking forward
to finishing this today.

397
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:55,625
Damn it. Let's go home.

398
00:18:55,708 --> 00:18:57,583
Huh? Did I hear that right?

399
00:18:57,666 --> 00:18:59,166
Did he say they're
gonna just leave?

400
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,125
That's what it
sounded like to me.

401
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:04,708
[gasps, whimpers]
Yes! That's amazing!

402
00:19:04,791 --> 00:19:06,333
We're safe and we
don't have to fight.

403
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:08,333
Uh, yeah. But...

404
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:14,416
I have a real bad feeling
about this, Midoriya.

405
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:16,208
It seems weird that they'd
retreat at this point,

406
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:18,583
even if help is on the way.

407
00:19:18,666 --> 00:19:20,250
[IZUKU]
All Might's probably coming.

408
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:22,041
Don't they wanna kill him?

409
00:19:22,125 --> 00:19:25,041
They must know UA will beef up
their security after this.

410
00:19:25,125 --> 00:19:26,958
So now's their best chance.

411
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:28,333
What's going on here?

412
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:30,583
Why is this "game over," huh?

413
00:19:31,666 --> 00:19:33,791
[SHIGARAKI]
Oh, before we leave,

414
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:37,583
let's make sure the
Symbol of Peace is broken.

415
00:19:37,666 --> 00:19:39,500
Let's wreck his pride.

416
00:19:39,583 --> 00:19:40,708
[gasps]

417
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:44,166
[SHIGARAKI]
Let's make this hurt.

418
00:20:00,958 --> 00:20:03,708
[SHIGARAKI]
You really are so cool...

419
00:20:04,875 --> 00:20:06,875
[AIZAWA grunting]

420
00:20:06,958 --> 00:20:09,625
[SHIGARAKI]
...Eraser Head.

421
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:12,125
[AIZAWA groans]

422
00:20:12,208 --> 00:20:14,250
[IZUKU]
Crap, crap, crap, crap, crap!

423
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:17,125
This guy's clearly different
from the ones we fought before!

424
00:20:17,208 --> 00:20:20,208
I've gotta save Asui
and get us outta here!

425
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:25,125
You! Let her go! Now! Smash!

426
00:20:27,083 --> 00:20:28,541
[VILLAINS yelp]

427
00:20:32,541 --> 00:20:39,666
[IZUKU panting]

428
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:42,083
[IZUKU]
What? My arm's not broken.

429
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:45,000
I can't believe it!
After all that training,

430
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:47,625
now's when I'm able to
get a good Smash in?

431
00:20:47,708 --> 00:20:48,875
All right!

432
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:54,583
[IZUKU gasps]
Where'd he come from?

433
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:58,625
Wait, hold on.
It didn't... hurt him?

434
00:21:00,208 --> 00:21:01,625
If the villains
spent so much time

435
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:02,958
planning this attack,

436
00:21:03,041 --> 00:21:05,708
then they probably figured
out a way to kill him.

437
00:21:05,791 --> 00:21:07,833
[IZUKU]
No way...

438
00:21:07,916 --> 00:21:10,000
[SHIGARAKI]
You're pretty powerful.

439
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:11,958
This "smash" of yours...

440
00:21:12,041 --> 00:21:14,916
Are you one of
All Might's disciples?

441
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:18,875
Doesn't matter. I'm
done with you now.

442
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:21,208
[gasping]

443
00:21:21,291 --> 00:21:24,125
[IZUKU yelps]

444
00:21:24,208 --> 00:21:25,250
Ribbit!

445
00:21:44,791 --> 00:21:47,375
[IZUKU grunts, gasps]

446
00:21:54,458 --> 00:21:56,125
[ASHIDO, OCHACO gasp]

447
00:22:06,083 --> 00:22:08,708
[ALL MIGHT]
Have no fear, students.

448
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,791
I am here!

449
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:17,666
Look, we're saved!

450
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:19,375
Ribbit.

451
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:24,291
He's here... All Might...

452
00:22:32,291 --> 00:22:34,250
[SHIGARAKI]
Ah.

453
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:38,291
Looks like our game's
getting a "continue."

454
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:12,708
[ALL MIGHT]
Don't worry, class. I am here!

455
00:24:12,791 --> 00:24:14,375
[IZUKU]
Next time: "All Might."

456
00:24:14,458 --> 00:24:16,625
[ALL MIGHT] Not to spoil
things, but these evildoers

457
00:24:16,708 --> 00:24:19,041
are going to be hitting
my weak spots pretty hard!

458
00:24:19,125 --> 00:24:20,458
[IZUKU]
Go beyond!

459
00:24:20,541 --> 00:24:22,875
[IZUKU, ALL MIGHT]
Plus Ultra!

